[bq="liamwhite1"]JFYI, forum pagination is broken because we don't want to have 13-20 second page load times in the bigger forums. You'll probably have to live with it being broken like this for a while, because the fact that simple mathematical logic breaks down like this on production has made this code unsalvageable.[/bq]

At work we have a test that runs on production machines every hour:

@function test_pi() {
    $pi = 3.1415926535;
    $this->assertTrue($pi > 3);
    $this->assertTrue($pi < 4);
}@

We had to disable nagios alerts on it because it started failing so often. Language: PHP.
